{{Infobox comedian | name = Janey Godley | image = JaneyBAFTA08.jpg | imagesize = | caption = Godley at the [[BAFTA]] Awards in 2008 | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1961|1|20}} | birth_place = Glasgow, Scotland | website = [http://www.janeygodley.co.uk Official website]}}
'''Janey Godley''' (born 20 January 1961) is a Scottish stand-up comedian and writer from [[Calton, Glasgow|Calton]], [[Glasgow]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.scotsman.com/news/petrol-bomb-pensioner-shows-old-gang-hatreds-die-hard-1-1072606|title=Petrol bomb pensioner shows old gang hatreds die hard|publisher=The Scotsman|date=6 January 2008|accessdate=30 September 2017}}</ref>
== Career ==
Godley began her stand up career in 1994.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chortle.co.uk/comics/j/508/janey_godley|title=Janey Godley, comedian : Chortle : The UK Comedy Guide|last=Solutions|first=Powder Blue Internet Business|website=www.chortle.co.uk|access-date=2017-03-20}}</ref> She won an award for the "Best Show Concept" at the [[New Zealand International Comedy Festival]] in 2002, and the "Spirit of the Festival" in 2006.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chortle.co.uk/comics/j/508/janey_godley|title=Janey Godley, comedian : Chortle : The UK Comedy Guide|last=Solutions|first=Powder Blue Internet Business|website=www.chortle.co.uk|access-date=2017-02-19}}</ref> In 2005 her autobiography ''Handstands in the Dark'' was published.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.randomhouse.co.uk/catalog/author.htm?authorID=5302|title=''Handstands in the Dark'' listing at Random House|accessdate=14 February 2016}}</ref> In 2006, she was a finalist for the Edinburgh Evening Times'"Scotswoman of the Year" award.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pressreader.com/uk/evening-times/20061018/281977488114311|title=Last chance to vote for Scotswoman of the Year|last=Robertson|first=Linda|date=18 October 2006|newspaper=Evening Times|access-date=19 February 2017|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|work=|via=}}</ref> In 2002, 2006, 2008 and 2009, she was nominated as "Best International Guest" by the New Zealand Comedy Guild.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.scottishcomedyagency.com/janey-godly|title=Janey Godley|website=Scottish Comedy Agency|language=en-US|access-date=2017-02-19}}</ref>
== Family == Her daughter [[Ashley Storrie]] is also a stand-up comedian,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.list.co.uk/article/81277-interview-ashley-storrie-i-have-been-known-to-go-a-bit-tonto/|title=Interview: Ashley Storrie – ‘I have been known to go a bit Tonto’|date=2016-06-08|newspaper=The List|access-date=2017-02-19|language=en-GB}}</ref> and the two have worked together, both in support of the [[National Autistic Society]] of Scotland,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thenational.scot/news/14958355.Autistic_acts_trained_by_Janey_Godley_aim_to_raise_a_few_laughs/|title=Autistic acts trained by Janey Godley aim to raise a few laughs|website=The National|language=en|access-date=2017-02-19}}</ref> as well as performing together at the [[Edinburgh Fringe]] in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://au.blouinartinfo.com/news/story/1473474/top-8-shows-at-edinburgh-fringe-2016|title=Top 8 Shows at Edinburgh Fringe 2016|last=Beech|first=Mark|date=3 August 2016|website=BLOUINARTINFO|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=19 February 2017}}</ref>
== Political activism == In February 2016 Godley joined a group of comedians on a tour of the UK in support of Labour party leader [[Jeremy Corbyn]], although she is a supporter of the [[Scottish National Party]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/comedian-janey-godley-on-tour-to-make-jeremy-corbyn-prime-minister-admits-to-being-an-snp-member-a6852336.html|title=Comedian on Jeremy Corbyn's #JC4PM tour has said she would never vote for him|date=2016-02-03|newspaper=The Independent|access-date=2017-02-19|language=en-GB}}</ref>
In 2016 Godley, was pictured standing outside [[Donald Trump]]'s [[Turnberry (golf course)|Turnberry Golf resort]] holding a sign which stated "Trump is a Cunt" went viral. She was prevented from approaching her subject by [[Police Scotland]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thenational.scot/news/14896567.Comedian_Janey_Godley_plans_Glasgow_Against_Trump_rally_in_George_Square/|title=Comedian Janey Godley plans Glasgow Against Trump rally in George Square|website=The National|language=en|access-date=2017-02-19}}</ref> Following a protest in Glasgow which she organised in November 2016 just prior to [[United States presidential election, 2016|the election of Trump as President]], she received rape threats through [[Twitter]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.glasgowlive.co.uk/news/glasgow-news/glaswegian-comedian-janey-godley-threatened-12136634|title=Glaswegian Janey Godley threatened with rape after George Square Trump protest|last=Gilbert|first=Julie|date=2016-11-06|newspaper=glasgowlive|access-date=2017-02-19}}</ref>
